  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Haiyan Emergency Response Program: Distribution of Water Filtration Units</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In response to the need for access to safe drinking water following Typhoon Haiyan, LWR is implementing WASH activities to help prevent the outbreak and spread of disease. 

LWR is installing 240 community water filtration units in child-centered spaces&#x2014;such as schools and day care centers&#x2014;to ensure that communities have access to safe drinking water in the storm&#x2019;s aftermath. 

In total, LWR expects to reach up to 60 schools with the units, as well as up to 60 day care centers. Thus far, 20 units have been installed. Schools and day care centers are currently on break for summer vacation. To prepare for the resumption of classes in June, units are being pre-positioned so that they will be ready and fully operational once children return to school in June. 

Teachers and day care center facilitators are receiving training on how to operate and maintain the units so that they can be used for months to come.</narrative>
  </description>
